title: ‘White Wolf and the Dragon Queen’ Update
body:
The Bran chapter is a work in progress guys, but writer’s block is properly kicking my arse at the minute. Honeslty, it takes me ages to find the words to write and then nearly every sentence I write just doesn’t seem right.

As a tease to keep you going until I post it, there will be more information on what the Night King and his army have been doing North of the Wall and also on Bran’s vision of Jon

Sorry everyone. I’ll get the chapter up ASAP

Robb: Well, I'd probably try to save both of you.

Theon: If you...
body:
Theon: Suppose me and Jon were drowning. Who would you save?

Robb: Well, I’d probably try to save both of you.

Theon: If you could only save one of us.

Robb: Then I’d save Jon, because I know for a fact that you, Theon, can swim.

Theon: Suppose I was holding an anchor.

Robb: Can’t you let go of the anchor?

Theon: …it’s a family heirloom.

Robb: I’m leaving.

title: [SPOILERS] The Red Woman
body:
Hey guys, long term lurker here. I love this sub and spend most days reading all your theories. This is only for people who are up to date with the show.

I’ve been watching back some of the show recently and I wanted to ask you all, what do you think will happen (if anything) with Melisandre in the final season? Do you think she may have an important role to play? Or is her work done after what happened with Jon and her purpose is served? She’s been almost constant in different storylines throughout the show, so it will be interesting to find out what GRRM plans to do with her



Source: https://ift.tt/2MiZJcv

summary: Imagine being of House Bolton and being betrothed to a Stark. Summary: You have arrived in Winterfell and feast with the Starks....
caption:
Imagine being of House Bolton and being betrothed to a Stark.

Summary: You have arrived in Winterfell and feast with the Starks. You meet the first son of Eddard and Catelyn Stark, Robb Stark. 

Warning(s): None

Word Count: 391

“How long have we been waiting for this Robb Stark?” You asked your companion. The feast started at the order of Eddard Stark, saying his first-born would be in attendance soon. 

Catelyn noticed your irritancy though you masked it with a smile. She ordered Theon to find Robb. You took it upon yourself to socialize with the girls of the Stark House. Catelyn called up her daughter Sansa before you.

“And your name is Sansa, right?” When she nodded you smiled. “Beautiful name for a beautiful girl.”

“Thank you, Lady Bolton,” Sansa bowed.

You nodded. “Lady Bolton was my mother, Y/N, please.” Sansa blushed, glad to have your first name. You sat with her and her friend for the next few minutes.

“So, Sansa, tell me about your brother Robb. Is he always this punctual?” Sansa giggled and so did you.

Sansa told you that Robb was a man of honor and duty, much like their father. Before she got too deep into the story of Robb Stark, his name echoed in the dining hall.

You and Sansa stood from your table, watching him walk up to the frontmost table to his parents. He muttered something to his father, but the look on his mother’s face meant more than an excuse. Ned waved you over as Robb kept his back to you.

“Y/N Bolton, this is my first-born son, Robb,” Ned motioned. Robb bowed to you as you followed.

Once Robb laid eyes on you, he was beyond taken. He extended his hand asking for a dance. You gladly took his palm, not surprised at all that he was attractive.

He led you to the center of the hall and bowed before you. He took you into his arm and lead you around the space.

“Please forgive my tardiness,” Robb uttered. “I wanted to be sure I was worthy of your appearance.” You blushed slightly at his need to impress you.

He stood much taller than you– his shoulder passing your brow and his strides much longer. He held the midsection of your back against his large and warm hand. You could tell dancing wasn’t a strong suit for him, but important enough to learn and remember.

“Your sister tells me that you’re a man of duty and honor, I can deal with a lack of punctuality once in a while.”
